      "date": "2011-07-14 21:31:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: (1 inline comment)\n\nBesides the comment I wrote, there is a similar issue if we umount a client and mount it again immediately, the mount may fail because a duplicate mgs is found in stopping state. Can you please combine the following patch with yours?\n\ndiff --git a/lustre/obdclass/obd_mount.c b/lustre/obdclass/obd_mount.c\nindex e92d1c2..339bcc9 100644\n--- a/lustre/obdclass/obd_mount.c\n+++ b/lustre/obdclass/obd_mount.c\n@@ -859,6 +859,9 @@ static int lustre_stop_mgc(struct super_block *sb)\n         if (!niduuid)\n                 GOTO(out, rc = -ENOMEM);\n \n+        /* make sure mgc has really gone */\n+        obd_zombie_barrier();\n+\n         for (i = 0; i < lsi->lsi_lmd->lmd_mgs_failnodes; i++) {\n                 sprintf(ptr, \"_%x\", i);\n                 rc = do_lcfg(LUSTRE_MGC_OBDNAME, 0, LCFG_DEL_UUID,",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
